India Allows Infrastructure Companies to Refinance Rupee Loans

-- B y   A n u r a g   J o s h i
-- 
2011-09-25T07:06:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-25/india-allows-infrastructure-companies-to-refinance-rupee-loans.html
India  is to allow infrastructure
companies to use as much as 25 percent of overseas borrowing to
refinance rupee loans, according to the central bank.  Infrastructure companies need to spend at least 75 percent
of borrowing from abroad on capital expenditure on projects, the
 Reserve Bank  of India said in a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anurag Joshi in Mumbai at 
